bigint :- When creating a migration using Ruby on Rails and MySQL, the default MySQL type created when defining an integer field is an 11-digit signed int . This will allow you to store signed integers up to 2147483647. However MySQL has the BIGINT storage type which stores signed integers up to 9223372036854775807

